Barys Hockey Club (Kazakh: Барыс хоккей клубы, romanized: Barys Hokkei Kluby), commonly referred to as Barys Nur-Sultan (formerly Barys Astana) or simply Barys, is a professional ice hockey team based in Nur-Sultan, Kazakhstan. It is one of the founding members of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL). They play in the league’s Chernyshev Division of the Eastern Conference. Their home arena is the Barys Arena, where they have played since the 2015–16 KHL season.
